  "description": "Company's merging and renaming process: dmp (Dwango Music Publishing) -> dmARTS -> due (Dwango User Entertainment) -> U&R Records -> Netmune\n\n> **Dwango User Entertainment, Inc.** was a record company formerly owned by **Dwango**. It was headquartered in Chuo-ku, Tokyo.\nIt mainly released CDs related to anime and video games.\nDistribution was outsourced to major distributors **Geneon** (**NBCUniversal Entertainment Japan LLC**) and **Avex Music Creative Inc.**, and indie distributors such as **Daiki Sound Co., Ltd.**. It was absorbed into **Dwango Co., Ltd.** on November 1, 2014.\n\n*-Wikipedia*",
